               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17861025-99-person1237">
                  JOSEPH
                   NICHOLSON
               <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1237" type="surname" value="NICHOLSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1237" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1237" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw a gentleman going on quietly; I<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178610250176"></xptr> watched the two prisoners, who followed him; I am sure they were in company together; I heard them converse together; then the prisoner Bass put his hand into the gentleman's pocket, and took out the handkerchief, and gave it to the prisoner Ferrill; as soon as they had done this, they both run away; I told the watchman to take them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Did not you stop another man, and then let him go? - Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17861025-99-person1238">
                  JOHN
                   NEWMAN
               <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1238" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1238" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I found this handkerchief in the prisoner's bosom.</p>
               <p>PRISONER FERRILL'S DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>My brother gave me the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17861025-99-person1239">
                  WILLIAM
                   BASS
               <interp inst="t17861025-99-person1239" type="surname" value="BASS"></interp>
